    <section>
      <h2>How They Actually Differ</h2>

      <h3>Workflow</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Browse specialized remote/hybrid job board, get AI-matched jobs, review tailored resume for each position, approve and apply—all in one platform. Focused on application quality.</p>
      <p><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> Build professional profile, network with connections, browse job listings, apply through external company sites or LinkedIn's application system. Networking-first approach.</p>

      <h3>Automation vs Manual Effort</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> AI tailors resumes automatically for each job. You review each one (30-60 seconds) before applying. Job matching happens automatically based on your profile.</p>
      <p><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> Requires manual profile optimization, networking, and job browsing. No automatic resume tailoring. You must customize applications yourself or use the same profile/resume for all.</p>

      <h3>Output Quality</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Each resume is tailored to match specific job requirements with ATS optimization. Higher interview rates because applications are precisely targeted.</p>
      <p><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> Uses your profile or uploaded resume for all applications. No per-job customization unless you manually edit. Quality depends on your profile optimization skills.</p>

      <h3>Learning Curve</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Simple setup—create profile, upload resume, start browsing. The platform guides you through tailoring and applications.</p>
      <p><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> Requires learning profile optimization, networking etiquette, and platform features. Steeper learning curve for effective use.</p>

      <h3>Friction Points</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Requires reviewing each tailored resume (adds 30-60 seconds per application). Smaller job pool focused on remote/hybrid roles. No networking features.</p>
      <p><strong>LinkedIn:</strong> Highly competitive—hundreds of applicants per job. No automatic resume tailoring. Requires networking and profile maintenance. Premium features cost extra.</p>
